BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ah_R0sv8RPJftnHr8Q52d
SUMMARY:CL 101: Intro to Concert Lighting
DTSTAMP:20260326T050320Z
DTSTART:20260606T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:In this 2-hour workshop\, students will have a practical grasp 
	on lighting concepts and console operation\, learn about different lightin
	g instruments\, and gain hands-on experience programming lights for Vera’s
	 mainstage. Participants of the class will also gain basic fundamental kno
	wledge of working with artists and production staff to elevate the concert
	 experience as a lighting engineer.\n\nComplete this class to be eligible 
	for Lighting Engineer volunteer shifts at Vera shows. Become a volunteer a
	t Vera to access other production-related opportunities!\n\nhttps://link.d
	ice.fm/nd0a20050763\n\nFrom The Vera Project
URL:https://link.dice.fm/nd0a20050763
LOCATION:305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, Washington 98109\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:vera-project
CATEGORIES:The Vera Project
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
